      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you might have experienced a caffeine-induced headache or perhaps mild dehydration. While it's true that caffeine can cause tension headaches and dehydration can contribute to headaches, the suddenness of your experience is unusual. I would suggest you drink a glass of water and take it easy for the rest of the day. If the headache returns or worsens, consider reducing your coffee intake and staying well-hydrated. Rest is also a good idea, but if symptoms persist, it might be wise to consult a healthcare professional.",
